<paragraph blockId="29.[138,1185,1369,1685]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">
The male gonothecae of this species have not been described so far. As for many other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oken" authorityYear="1815" box="[138,243,1402,1426]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[138,243,1402,1426]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">Halecium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, their morphology differs from the female ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[138,1185,1369,1685]" lastBlockId="30.[125,1173,136,511]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="636" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">
<bibRefCitation author="Patriti G" box="[165,328,1434,1458]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref15696" refString="Patriti G. 1970. Catalogue des cnidaires et ctenaires des cotes Atlantiques marocaines. Travaux de l'Institut scientifique cherifien, Serie zoologie 35: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1970">Patriti (1970)</bibRefCitation>
identified closely similar colonies from 
<collectingCountry box="[809,914,1434,1458]" name="Morocco" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">Morocco</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trebilcock" authorityYear="1928" box="[960,1177,1434,1458]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="corrugatissimum">
<emphasis box="[960,1177,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">H. corrugatissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The hydrothecae of her material were clearly everted and therefore her material was more likely 
<taxonomicName authority="(M. Sars, 1857)" baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[209,618,1499,1523]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[209,413,1499,1523]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">Halecium pusillum</emphasis>
(M. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sars M" box="[479,609,1499,1523]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" pagination="110 - 164" refId="ref15996" refString="Sars M. 1857. Bidrag til kundskaben om middelhavets Littoral-Fauna, Reisebemaerkninger fra Italien, I Classis: Polypi. Nyt Magazin for Naturvidenskaberne 9: 110 - 164." type="journal article" year="1857">Sars, 1857</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a well-known Mediterranean species. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">Halecium pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trebilcock" authorityYear="1928" box="[457,674,1532,1556]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="corrugatissimum">
<emphasis box="[457,674,1532,1556]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">H. corrugatissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but usually has everted hydrothecae (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Broch H" box="[138,276,1564,1588]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" pagination="1 - 65" refId="ref13851" refString="Broch H. 1912. Hydroiduntersuchungen: III, Vergleichende Studien an Adriatischen Hydroiden. Konglige Norske Videnskaberne Selskabs Skrifter (1911) 1: 1 - 65." type="journal article" year="1912">Broch 1912</bibRefCitation>
for re-description of the 
<typeStatus box="[569,618,1564,1588]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">type</typeStatus>
material; 
<bibRefCitation author="Babic K" box="[737,870,1563,1588]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" pagination="468 - 474" refId="ref13469" refString="Babic K. 1913. Ueber einige Haleciiden. Zoologischer Anzeiger 41: 468 - 474." type="journal article" year="1913">Babić 1913</bibRefCitation>
for figures of gonothecae). 
<bibRefCitation author="Motz-Kossowska S" box="[138,423,1596,1620]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" pagination="325 - 352" refId="ref15377" refString="Motz-Kossowska S. 1911. Contribution a la connaissance des hydraires de la Mediterranee occidentale: II, Hydraires calyptoblastiques. Archives de Zoologie Experimentale et Generale 6: 325 - 352." type="journal article" year="1911">Motz-Kossowska (1911)</bibRefCitation>
attributed similar, but infertile, colonies to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[919,1047,1596,1620]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[919,1047,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">H. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, despite the hydrothecae having straight walls. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stechow E" box="[552,741,1629,1653]" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" pagination="1 - 172" refId="ref16179" refString="Stechow E. 1919. Zur Kenntnis der Hydroidenfauna des Mittelmeeres, Amerikas und anderer Gebiete, nebst Angaben uber einige Kirchenpauer'sche Typen von Plumulariden. Zoologische Jahrbucher. Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 42: 1 - 172." type="journal article" year="1919">Stechow (1919)</bibRefCitation>
therefore considered this material to belong to a separate species which he named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Torrey" authorityYear="1902" box="[670,902,1661,1685]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="29" pageNumber="635" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="annulatum">
<emphasis box="[670,902,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="635">Halecium annulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because this name was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName authority="Torrey, 1902" authorityName="Torrey" authorityYear="1902" box="[308,625,136,160]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="annulatum">
<emphasis box="[308,463,136,160]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. annulatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Torrey HB" box="[469,625,136,160]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref16286" refString="Torrey HB. 1902. The Hydroida of the Pacific Coast of North America. University of California Publications Zoology 1: 1 - 104, Plates 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1902">Torrey, 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Leloup E" box="[636,804,136,160]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref14989" refString="Leloup E. 1938. Quelques hydraires des cotes orientale et occidentale des Etats-Unis. Bulletin du Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique 14: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1938">Leloup (1938)</bibRefCitation>
changed it to 
<taxonomicName box="[965,1164,136,160]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="stechoaei">
<emphasis box="[965,1164,136,160]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">Halecium stechoaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero AL &amp; Garcia Carrascosa AM" box="[125,691,168,192]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref15725" refString="Pena Cantero AL, Garcia Carrascosa AM. 2002. The benthic hydroid fauna of the Chafarinas Islands (Alboran Sea, western Mediterranean). Zoologische Verhandelingen 337: 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="2002">Peña Cantero and García Carrascosa (2002)</bibRefCitation>
also attributed the records of Motz- Kossowska (1911), hence 
<taxonomicName box="[439,568,200,224]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="stechoaei">
<emphasis box="[439,568,200,224]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. stechoaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[620,751,200,224]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[620,751,200,224]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The presence of the characteristic vegetative propagules in the material of 
<bibRefCitation author="Motz-Kossowska S" box="[649,945,232,256]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" pagination="325 - 352" refId="ref15377" refString="Motz-Kossowska S. 1911. Contribution a la connaissance des hydraires de la Mediterranee occidentale: II, Hydraires calyptoblastiques. Archives de Zoologie Experimentale et Generale 6: 325 - 352." type="journal article" year="1911">Motz-Kossowska (1911)</bibRefCitation>
makes this quite reasonable, but allowing also straight hydrothecae for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[762,891,264,288]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[762,891,264,288]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
narrows uncomfortably the gap to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trebilcock" authorityYear="1928" box="[253,468,295,319]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="corrugatissimum">
<emphasis box="[253,468,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. corrugatissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[125,1173,136,511]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">
Another nominal species in this complex is 
<taxonomicName authority="Nutting, 1901" authorityName="Nutting" authorityYear="1901" box="[661,1057,328,352]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis box="[661,879,328,352]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">Halecium speciosum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nutting CC" box="[888,1057,328,352]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" pagination="157 - 216" refId="ref15661" refString="Nutting CC. 1901. Papers from the Harriman Alaska Expedition: XXI, The hydroids. Proceedings of the Washington Academy of Science 3: 157 - 216, pls 14 - 26." type="journal article" year="1901">Nutting, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species originally described from 
<collectingRegion box="[434,510,360,384]" country="United States of America" name="Alaska" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">Alaska</collectingRegion>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser CM" box="[635,784,360,384]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" refId="ref14455" refString="Fraser CM. 1937. Hydroids of the Pacific coast of Canada and the United States. Toronto: The University of Toronto Press. 208 p, 44 plates." type="book" year="1937">Fraser 1937</bibRefCitation>
). Considering their climatic and geographic separation, it appears unlikely to me that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trebilcock" authorityYear="1928" box="[731,943,391,415]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="corrugatissimum">
<emphasis box="[731,943,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. corrugatissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[958,1085,391,415]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusillum">
<emphasis box="[958,1085,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. pusillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nutting" authorityYear="1901" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="30" pageNumber="636" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="speciosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">H. speciosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to the same biological species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[125,1173,136,511]" pageId="30" pageNumber="636">These three nominal species are likely another example of the limitations we must be aware of when we attempt to discriminate biological species by morphological characters.</paragraph>
